<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-58-0160 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper deals with the investigation of optical and mechanical propertiesof polycrystalline fibers from silver and thallium halide crystals. Thedependence of the fiber properties on the fabrication conditions, aswell as the influence of the stretching stresses and UV irradiation onthe optical losses, are discussed. The fabrication of the first AgCl-claddedKRS-13 fibers is reported. 10 references.</TEXT></DOC>